Creates a database connection on the given connection string and tests that it can be opened and closed. If it can't, the error code returned by MySqlException is returned by this function.
Executes a filter query built by a forms.dialogs.AdvancedFilter dialog.

simplesect.para: A DataTable containing all of the rows that matched the query.
It is up to the calling class to parse this data appropiately.

parameterdescription.para: The table to get the columns of

simplesect.para: An ArrayList of type string containing the column names.

briefdescription.para: Run the _.show_table_status() stored prodedure to get information about tables.

simplesect.para: A DataTable ready to be used as a data source for a DataGridView Control.

briefdescription.para: Get the last row id inserted in the specified table.

briefdescription.para: Inserts a new client into the database.

simplesect.para: True if the record was inserted successfully; False otherwise.

briefdescription.para: Attempts to insert a new record into the File table. If the insert could not be completed, the transaction is rolled back and no data is committed to the database.

simplesect.para: The row id of the inserted file; 0 if the file was not inserted.

briefdescription.para: Update the CFile object in the database. If the file has an ID of 0, it is inserted instead.

simplesect.para: True if the update/insert completed successfully. False otherwise.

briefdescription.para: Retrieve a single CFile record from the database.

parameterdescription.para: The id of the file record.

simplesect.para: A single CFile object representing the file record or null if no file was found

briefdescription.para: Retrieves multiple files from the database based on the supplied ids.

parameterdescription.para: A variable length parameter: the list of ids of the file records to retrieve.

simplesect.para: A List<T> of type CFile containing the file objects or an empty List<T> if no files were found

briefdescription.para: Attempts to delete a file record from the database.
